status: success
Summary:
On November 14, 2024, an unauthorized actor accessed the production database using compromised service account credentials that had been accidentally exposed in a public GitHub repository. The attacker exfiltrated 12,400 user records containing names, email addresses, and bcrypt-hashed passwords. The incident was contained within 6 hours, credentials were rotated, affected users were notified, and regulatory filings were submitted.
